{
  "texts": [
    "However, the extensive use of AI in pandemic response raises ethical concerns.",
    "Data privacy must be protected, algorithmic biases mitigated, transparency and accountability ensured, and individual autonomy and informed consent maintained.",
    "AI has improved early detection and reaction processes, enabling worldwide collaboration via monitoring networks across geopolitical boundaries.",
    "Real-world applications like ProMED-Mail and BlueDot demonstrate the real influence of AI in anticipating epidemics and guiding response operations.",
    "A cautious approach to AI use, balancing proactive readiness and individual rights, is still required."
  ]
}